Destination XL Group, Inc. Key Developments

Destination XL Group, Inc. Announces Board Retirements
Jun 23 17
On June 20, 2017, each of Jesse Choper and George Porter, Jr. notified Destination XL Group, Inc. that they would not stand for re-election to the Company's Board of Directors at the Company's Annual Meeting of Stockholders to be held on August 3, 2017. Messrs. Choper and Porter will remain on the Board until the Annual Meeting and until their successors are elected and qualified.


Destination XL Group, Inc. Presents at Jefferies 2017 Global Consumer Conference, Jun-21-2017 10:30 AM
Jun 8 17
Destination XL Group, Inc. Presents at Jefferies 2017 Global Consumer Conference, Jun-21-2017 10:30 AM. Venue: White Elephant Hotel, Nantucke, Massachusetts, United States. Speakers: David A. Levin, Chief Executive Officer, President & Director, Peter H. Stratton, CFO, Senior VP & Treasurer.


Destination XL Group, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended April 29, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Year Fiscal Year 2017
May 19 17
Destination XL Group, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended April 29, 2017. For the quarter, total sales declined slightly to $107.7 million from $107.9 million in the prior year’s first quarter. The decrease of $0.2 million in total sales was due to a comparable sales decrease of $2.1 million, or 2.1% compared to a comparable sales increase of 2.0% last year. Net loss was $6.1 million, or $0.12 per basic and diluted share, compared with net income of $0.2 million, or $0.00 per basic and diluted share, for the prior year’s first quarter. On a non-GAAP basis, assuming a normalized tax rate of 40%, adjusted net loss was $0.07 per diluted share compared with net income of $0.00 per diluted share for the prior year’s first quarter. The decline in earnings was driven primarily by a combination of higher planned marketing costs related to television advertising campaign as well as lower gross margin dollar contribution due to occupancy de-leverage. Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization, a non-GAAP measure, were $2.5 million, compared with $8.4 million for the first quarter of fiscal 2016. Cash flow used in operations was $4.6 million, compared with $5.0 million for the first quarter of fiscal 2016. Capital expenditures were $6.9 million and consisted of $5.8 million for new DXL stores and $1.1 million for infrastructure projects. Capital expenditures for the first quarter of fiscal 2016 of $6.1 million consisted of $4.6 million for new DXL stores and $1.5 million for infrastructure projects. Free cash flow, a non-GAAP measure, decreased slightly to negative $11.5 million from negative $11.1 million for the first quarter of fiscal 2016. Operating loss was $5,234,000 against operating income of $1,055,000 a year ago. Loss before provision for income taxes was $6,036,000 against income of before provision for income taxes $271,000 a year ago. 

The company provided earnings guidance for the year fiscal year 2017. For the year, the company expects net loss (GAAP basis) of $5.7 million to $11.7 million, depreciation and amortization of $32.5 million, EBITDA (non-GAAP basis) of $24.0 million to $30.0 million, net loss per diluted share of $0.11 to $0.23, adjusted net loss of $3.4 million to $7.0 million, adjusted net loss per share of $0.06 to $0.14, cash flow from operating activities of $37.0 million to $42.0 million, capital expenditures, infrastructure projects $8.3 million, free cash flow, before DXL capital expenditures (non-GAAP basis) of $28.7 million to $33.7 million, capital expenditures for DXL stores of $13.7 million and free cash flow (non-GAAP basis) of $15.0 million to $20.0 million. The company expects income tax benefit, assuming 40% rate of $2.3 million to $4.7 million and interest expense of $3.0 million.


